## Abstract
**ASHI-CORE** (Autonomous Early Warning System for Information Collapse) is an aerospace-grade analytical framework engineered for the predictive detection of critical phase transitions in high-entropy complex systems. 

The system identifies divergences from **asymptotic stability regimes** by quantifying **Information Percolation**. ASHI-CORE maps signal degradation from structural coherence to global stochastic noise, providing a deterministic lead-time prior to systemic collapse (LCO - Limit Cycle Oscillation failure).

